me
read
it
to
him."
Harriet
looked
grave.
"My
dear
Harriet,
you
must
not
refine
too
much
upon
this
charade.
You
will
betray
your
feelings
improperly,
if
you
are
too
conscious
and
too
quick,
and
appear
to
affix
more
meaning,
or
even
quite
all
the
meaning
which
may
be
affixed
to
it.
Do
not
